title: Сборная Сан-Марино победила в первый раз за 20 лет - Евро-Футбол
text: В Лиге наций провели матч сборные Сан-Марино и Лихтенштейна. Хозяева поля добились победы благодаря голу Никко Сенсоли на 53-й минуте. Это первая победа сан-маринцев за 20 лет и 140 матчей. Серия началась как раз с Лихтенштейна. title: Empowering the Future of Medicine: Announcing the Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors Winner | observernewsonline.com
text:
Dr. Mahmud Kara Valley View, Ohio - Dr. Mahmud Kara , a distinguished medical practitioner with over three decades of experience, is thrilled to announce the recipient of the inaugural Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors. This esteemed scholarship, established in recognition of Dr. Kara's remarkable contributions to the medical field, aims to nurture visionary minds in medicine.
The Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors offers undergraduate students across the nation a unique opportunity to showcase their innovative ideas and commitment to transforming healthcare. With a generous one-time award of $1,000, this scholarship not only honors academic excellence but also celebrates the potential impact that emerging doctors can have on the global healthcare landscape.
As part of the application process, the winner participated in an engaging essay contest, where they demonstrated their innovative approaches to healthcare and their commitment to positive change in the field.
The Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors serves as a beacon of hope and opportunity for aspiring medical professionals, transcending mere monetary recognition. Beyond its financial support, this scholarship embodies a profound commitment to nurturing the next wave of healthcare visionaries and leaders. It signifies a dedication to fostering a culture of excellence, compassion, and innovation within the medical community.
By providing this scholarship, Dr. Mahmud Kara aims to inspire and empower young minds to push the boundaries of conventional medicine, encouraging them to explore new avenues of research, treatment modalities, and patient care practices. This commitment to innovation is essential in addressing the evolving challenges and complexities of modern healthcare.
Moreover, the scholarship fosters a sense of community and collaboration among recipients, creating a network of like-minded individuals who share a passion for advancing healthcare and improving patient outcomes. Through mentorship, networking opportunities, and ongoing support, recipients of the Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors are encouraged to continue their journey of growth and development as compassionate healers and change-makers in the field of medicine.
Ultimately, this scholarship is not just about recognizing academic achievement; it is about investing in the future of healthcare. It is about nurturing the potential of young doctors to become leaders who will drive positive change, improve access to quality care, and make meaningful contributions to the well-being of individuals and communities worldwide. In this way, the Dr. Mahmud Kara Scholarship for Future Doctors embodies a profound commitment to shaping a brighter, healthier future for all.
Please join us in congratulating our winner for their outstanding achievement and in celebrating the bright future they embody for the field of medicine.
About Dr. Mahmud Kara :
Dr. Mahmud Kara is a highly esteemed medical professional with over three decades of experience. In 2017, he founded KaraMD, an online platform dedicated to supporting digestive health, heart health, and overall well-being. Dr. Kara's commitment to advancing medical knowledge and empowering future doctors continues to inspire individuals globally.

title: These NJ restaurants have both the best pizza and cheesesteaks
text: These NJ restaurants have both the best pizza and cheesesteaks As you know, I'm a bit of a cheesesteak aficionado. At least in my own head. Either way, I love a good cheesesteak and pizza. Some places have figured out the magic of combining the two. Delicious! When I brought this up on the air, our lines were flooded with calls about local go-to favorites around the Garden State. It's one of the reasons that I'm diggin' in. No way you're getting great pizza and cheesesteaks anywhere else. Here's the extended list for you to check out and hopefully try, at least one place on the list, this weekend! Make sure that if you have friends and family traveling in from other states to visit you for the holidays you don't let 'em leave before trying some delicious Jersey pizza! author: Michael J. Mawson, Bennington Banner
title: MAU girls dominate events to overcome numbers disadvantage, boys fall just short against Wahconah
text:
BENNINGTON — The small-but-mighty Mount Anthony swim teams continued their season Wednesday with a home meet against Wahconah.
The Patriots girls grinded out an 85-81 victory despite having only six swimmers to Wahconah’s 15. The MAU boys, outmanned 12-6, lost a tightly contested meet 81-79.
GIRLS
MAU won all but one of the 11 events, as Wahconah’s Emily Capoana swam to a victory in the 100 breaststroke with her time of 1:27.70, besting MAU’s Avery Camarda (1:28.86) by a second.
Camarda did record her victory in her only other individual event, the 200 individual medley (2:47.57), a full seven seconds ahead of the closest Warrior.
Emily Tibbetts (100 yard freestyle, 100 yard backstroke) and Lucy Poole (50 yard freestyle, 100 yard butterfly) won both of their individual events, while Olivia Crandall (200 yard freestyle) and Lucy Driscoll (500 yard freestyle) picked up one individual win.
The Patriots also benefited from winning all three relays. Nollyn Blair, Camarda, Poole and Tibbets teamed up to win the 200 medley relay by 11 seconds. It was Camarda, Crandall, Driscoll and Poole swimming to a nine-second win in the 200 yard freestyle relay while Blair, Driscoll, Crandall and Tibbetts took the 400 yard freestyle relay by a comfortable 24 seconds.
BOYS
MAU secured nine victories out of the 11-event meet, with the Warriors’ Artois Sancho claiming victory in the 50 yard freestyle and Kalen Spratt besting the field in the 100 yard backstroke.
The Patriots were led by Nixon Lebert and Braeden McManus, who each played a part in four of the victories. Lebert won both the 100 and 200 yard freestyle races, and was a part of MAU’s 200 medley and 400 freestyle relay teams.
McManus grabbed his individual wins in the 100 yard butterfly and the 200 individual medley, and also swam on the 200 medley relay team – along with Keegan Avienu and James Tock. McManus was also on the winning 200 freestyle relay team, along with Colin Joyce, Dan Wellspeak and Avienu.
Wellspeak added to the Patriots’ team score with his win in the 500 yard freestyle, as did Tock with a victory in the 100 yard breaststroke.
Both MAU teams are now 6-2 on the season as they prepare for Friday’s senior meet against Monument Mountain.

title: Cómo puede ayudar la tecnología a paliar la masificación turística
text:
La tecnología, aliada para paliar la masificación turística
Tecnología y datos contribuyen a ofrecer destinos alternativos al cliente dispuesto a aceptarlos
Publicada 13/03/25Gestores de destinos y proveedores turísticos tienen en la tecnología un gran aliado a la hora de reducir las situaciones de masificación y paliar así el impacto de la actividad turística en su entorno y sus consecuencias. Así se ha constatado en la mesa celebrada en la Convención ITB 2025 sobre “Viajes más inteligentes, destinos más fuertes: el papel de la tecnología en el crecimiento del turismo”, en la que han participado representantes de Expedia, UnderTheDoormat Group y Visit Oman.
